comment: Sometime in 1987, a 3 y/o girl from a small city in the Central Luzon Philippines always avidly perched herself up the wooden divider to be near an old radio waiting for Madonna's songs. True Blue was the one which always played repeatedly followed by La Isla Bonita. Later on in life while she was working in London sometime in 2009, she grabbed the chance to finally see Madonna in concert. It was one of the most memorable days of her life. Thank you for the joy your music brought to me, Madonna!

comment: I have been very fond and respectful of Madonna since I was fourteen in 1984. When I first heard the song "Borderline" on the radio, I realized that Madonna had something special, out of the ordinary, it was different from other pop music singers. And I was not mistaken! Time has shown me and everyone the great talent that Madonna had (and still has) inside her. Record successes, special talent for scandal and writing songs that to this day have remained in the memory and discography of many people who bought her records. It has set records never before achieved by any female artist, including the artist who has sold the most records ever, more than three hundred million, and concert records. Madonna's fortune is valued at over five hundred million! I have the honor of being one of Madonna's biggest fans. And I still have the great honor of having all the studio records, hit collections, the remix album You Can Dance from 1987, and two soundtracks of my favorite movies, Who's That Girl from 1987 too, and I'm Breathless from 1990. Congratulations, Madonna! You are my great queen of world pop music. No one can reach your Queen of Pop throne to this day! Thank you for your inspiration. Congratulations on your talent. Stay on your Queen of Pop throne forever! You're my favorite diva, my favorite queen of all the pop and rock queens in the world. Thank you so much for existing, for being my great inspiration, for helping me through the most difficult times of my life, for being the greatest and the best of all female artists since the eighties to this day, and I hope so forever! Thank you for your songs, your lyrics, your words, your controversies, your always inspiring attitudes! Luckily I have ALL your studio albums, Madonna! Luckily I have your four hit collections, the remixed album You Can Dance, and two soundtracks Who's That Girl and I'm Breathless, Madonna! Luckily I have the great honor of  one of your biggest fans! God bless you always my dear Queen! Congratulations my lovely Queen of Pop Music! You are the best female artist in the world! 👑💯‼️❤️💯‼️
author: Henrique Ramos

comment: True Blue was the best album Madonna ever released and even beats Like a Virgin, Like a Prayer, and Ray of Light in my and alot of her fans opinions. she was the strongest she has ever been vocally on True Blue and was the second time she went with a more soulful and raspy voice after she got a taste of it on Crazy For You.  Crazy For You  is my second favorite Madonna song after True Blue. its my favorite because when my partner was growing up this song got stuck in his head after hearing it on the radio in the summer of '86. it was the first song we ever claimed as our song. a month later it was changed to If My Heart Had Windows by patty Loveless. You see he has cerebral palsy and its harder for him to communicate his feelings so one night he sent me if my heart had windows via messenger and said this is how i feel about you......then one day we spotted a spot on his ear and it was melanoma cancer.  they cut it out and hacked his poor ear up and had to cut almost the whole earlobe off n give him a skin graft. that was 2 years ago. and the doctors told us that there was a 90% chance of it coming back and on his back more than likely. well 3 days ago i spotted a brown spot that had a fuzzy border, is asymetrical, brown in color, not all one color but multiple color. and it does not have any clear or well defined border. and theres tiny little red bumps on his back that could be nodular melanoma which has a high mortality rate. i am so scared, i cant imagine life without him. my brain just cant fathom it. he is 15 years older than me but i am 29 now and he is also 29 and holden he says lol we have made a pact that were going to stay 29 forever. We have been together 10 wonderful years in 2022, God willing. pray for him please🙏🏻 💖 ❤But we are living proof that True love, does indeed, still exist!!❤

comment: She was SO good in the 80s.  She just got weird in the 90s & has never been the same.  My favorite movie as a kid was 'Desperately Seeking Susan' because Madonna was in it & she was my idol.  9 year old me wanted those boots & that pyramid jacket so much.  The first album I ever owned was 'like a virgin'.  I memorized every track, even though I had no clue what a virgin even was.  She was beautiful, she could sing, she wasn't born an entitled snob -just a regular kid from Michigan, she had the best fashion sense, she had the most awesome name (Madonna Louise Veronica Ciccone).  She was the epitome of the 80s.

According to biographer Lucy O'Brien, True Blue album artwork was on-par with Andy Warhol's concept of PopArt: 
“The image was a mixture of innocence and idealism, while incorporating 1950s-style Technicolor and hand tinted color, characteristic of Warhol's silkscreen printed design, prevalent in the 1960s.” She added that, with this album, “Madonna made explicit the connection between Warhol and herself, the vivid nexus between pop art and commerce."
author: Gina Sousa Branco

comment:
Please don't be afraid to get older. I've read some comments about that.  It's a privilege to get older.  And yes, I miss the old days sometimes, like everyone else does at a certain age. But 6 years ago,  I was diagnosed with the same disease my mother died from in the early '90's and we shared music like this. But as a mother of a 7 year old boy, i'm just glad that i'm alive after 6 years of illness. It's a record in our family history.  So just be very thankfull for everyday you get older, and be very thankfull if you had a great childhood and if songs and artist like Madonna can bring you back in those times.  But also think of the future. Don't get stuck in the past. There is still lots of good music.  Madonna still makes great music.  Just be thankfull, even for the worst things in your life, because those things made you strong and made you remember what's really important in your life. 
DON'T FORGET YOUR PAST, BUT ENJOY YOUR TIMES AHEAD.
author: Marilyn

comment: Madonna was the first artist I became fan of. I used to listen to the album 'True blue' while playing with my He-man doll in bed, as it was to early to get up.  I had this little cassette recorder with me on my bed while enjoying the album.  But this song was the only song I didn't like.  But now, listening to it,  I like it. Still not one of my favorite Madonna songs, but I wouldn't skip the song.  ( Well i didn't skip this song back in the days because it was to hard. With cassettes you would wind to far and than had to go back, and then you went to far back!!!  Yes we had a hard, hard youth hahahaha )

comment: True blue was the first Madonna album I ever heard. My mom had the vinyl disc and would always play it. She told me her step-father (my grandpa) had given it to her. Note: my mom was very poor growing up and my grandpa had to borrow money just to get it for her 16th birthday. She still has it till this day and a CD form along with the immaculate collection and like a prayer. I'm so glad my mother showed me madonna's music. She said she was obsessed like everyone else in that decade. I'm so lucky that I'm one of a very few people born in the 2000s who admire madonna as much as I do thanks to my mom.

comment:
..ahh, the 80's....a little story, kids, if you can put up with me....back in the day, it was a PRIVILEGE to have ACTUAL cable, But, alas, we did not..... : ( 

THEN, we all were waiting with BATED breath, for the new Madonna Song / Video, which would be the follow-up to "Papa Don't Preach"; remember, NO INTERNET then... 'True Blue' was chosen as the 3rd single, Sept. '86, Madonna did a contest juncture with MTV called 'Make My Video', and the Winner will be chosen as the 'main video' that ALL music video outlets will show. Some young girl won, for her sepia-toned, 50's inspired video, and true to their word, all local non-cable stations played THAT version, as the 'main video'. 

BUT, word got out, that Madonna made an ACTUAL video (THIS version, for the European market) that was just  FABULOUS, and, EVERYONE wanted to see that version, but....it was not available to the US market (or people with NO cable.....)   : ( 

My mother came home from work early Friday night, and said she was VERY tired, and was going to bed early, and did NOT wanted to be disturbed... so, NO MUSIC VIDEO TAPING that night (Fridays was THE night to tape Music Videos in our home then); that same night, 'Friday Night Videos' on NBC, announced that they got a copy of the video, and was going to show it ONE TIME....I absolutely FLIPPED!! ....AND, MTV wasn't even gonna show it!  ...so, desperate, I decided to 'sneak' in my Mom's bedroom, to throw a blanket over the TV, and videotape the actual 'True' video (the main VCR was in her room)....but it was NOT to be...due to the fact, that Mom was doing "The Nasty" with a male co-worker she was having an affair with, that she snuck in through her back bedroom window!! ha-HAAA!!

I was FLABBERGASTED, watching that man, rolling naked all over my Mother!! ...to this DAY, the part, "True Love, oh, baby, baby..." (which was playing at the time I snuck in) shoots THAT memory back...THAT could've stayed in the 80's!!

 ......memmm-orieeeesss... X D

comment: I loved this album I begged and hinted that I would just die if I didn’t have this album for Christmas Then Christmas Day cane my Dad said it was sold out He looked everywhere I sorely disappointed So went to my Grandparents house for Our Annual Christmas Dinner had a great time with my family and friends Came home was getting ready for bed when my Dad said Treda (don’t ask Y he always called me that ) But I was like yes sir he said again sorry bout not getting the Madonna album I was like it’s ok From the corner of my eye I saw my Mother laffing I’m like wth in my head of course and he said can you get me a pop out the fridge...that’s weird so I opened the door and there it was  Brand new in clean clear plastic Madonna’s new album True Blue I was like Wooow gave both of them the biggest hug and they even let me listen to it on the Stereo system My dad had the baddest loudest stereo system on our street My Mother said not to loud and wear your earphones they were HUGE,,,,it was a Christmas I still gush about They saved the best for last Great Christmas

comment:
i am going to be a fan of this old song for the positive feeling i feel listening to this and with the video 
i had the cd for many many years  but i did not know this was an amazing and great song before i saw the  ciao Italy dvd to remember it :)
the music is in a bluesy mode (ternaire shuffle) and a big tribute to the songs of Motown
the feeling with this song is an incredible melody
a very sweet voice, she was young, something really pure in this song, not 100%innocent but not so sexy like after this period
we are very far from Erotica and others tunes :) 
This song with the voice and the melody brings me to something high, like a romantic side with an extreme softness in the voice and it's funny too ! a cool attitude .It's not the same 32 years later lol even she sings it yet with a ukulele
the song is something teenager ! it's very nice, beautiful, very sensible way to sing it touches hearts 
great melody and backing vocals

comment:
I was a little surprised when I saw this in the suggestions, and more so when I saw that there's also an entire album of the same name... I didn't remember it at all.

The reason was quickly revealed, as I listened; this tune is totally pedestrian, ordinary and there's no groove to speak of. The melody had already been done many times, several decades back, by the likes of Elvis etc. More like a tribute to some older 50's-60's rock ballads.

Forgettable, just as I did so.

comment: I was the costume designer and stylist on set for this video. Super-fun gig. Love to see it coming around again. This was shot on a sound stage in Queens, and directed by James Foley. Yup, THAT James Foley. Madonna's dress has 80 separate pieces sewn together so it would move beautifully, and she could dance without it shifting. No stretch material involved. Yes, that's Debi Mazar and the black girl is Erica, a frequent backup dancer for Madonna. The Latina's name I don't recall, she was someone's cute friend. At the time (1986), Madonna and Sean were very much in love, and an adorable couple.

«True Blue» —en español: «Incondicional» o «Fiel»— es una canción interpretada por la cantautora estadounidense Madonna, incluida en su tercer álbum de estudio, True Blue (1986).1 La compañía discográfica Sire Records la publicó como el tercer sencillo del disco el 29 de septiembre de 1986 en Europa, mientras que en los Estados Unidos, el 9 de octubre del mismo año.Compuesta inicialmente por Stephen Bray con la ayuda de Madonna en las letras, toma su nombre de una de las expresiones favoritas de su entonces esposo, el actor Sean Penn, y su visión muy pura del amor;  está dedicada directamente a él, como así también el álbum completo. Es una canción dance pop inspirada por las bandas femeninas de Motown de los años 1960. La instrumentación ofrece una guitarra rítmica, un teclado, acordes de sintetizador y la batería. El estribillo principal está respaldado por uno alternativo que incorpora una progresión de acordes de uso común en el género doo wop.
 En términos generales, recibió reseñas favorables de los periodistas y 
críticos musicales, quienes la calificaron como una «obra maestra» y la 
pista más alegre del álbum. Otros notaron su influencia en la música de los años 1950 y 1960, como así también de las bandas femeninas de esas décadas. Además, figuró en diversas listas de las mejores canciones de la cantante, elaboradas por revistas, periódicos y sitios web.Desde el punto de vista comercial, obtuvo un éxito en la mayor parte del mundo: alcanzó el primer lugar de las listas de Canadá, Irlanda, el Reino Unido y la Unión Europea, y llegó a los cinco primeros puestos en Australia, Bélgica, los Estados Unidos, Italia, Nueva Zelanda y los Países Bajos. Para la promoción del sencillo, se realizaron dos vídeos musicales: la versión oficial fue dirigida por James Foley y muestra a la intérprete con tres bailarinas interpretando y bailando el tema en un diner decorado de azul. La compañía Sire, junto con el canal de televisión MTV,
crearon un concurso llamado «Make My Video» con el objetivo de que los 
espectadores realizaran su propio videoclip de «True Blue».
Miles de personas presentaron sus cintas grabadas, y los vídeos finales
 seleccionados tenían una producción al estilo de los años 1950 y 
seguían la temática de la pista. Madonna interpretó el tema en la gira Who's That Girl World Tour de 1987 y 28 años después en el Rebel Heart Tour (2015-16).  Luego de su lanzamiento, varios artistas y bandas versionaron la canción, sobre todo para álbumes tributo.

http://ameblo.jp/galwayera/entry-12042074682.html
After having listened to this "True blue",  I felt awfully strong  4 beat like  "Stop in the name of love "  or "Baby love" of  Diana Ross.  They were called Motown sounds. Though each melody is different, We can imagine that the composer of "True blue", had slightly mimicked  that tune titled "Stop in the name of love".  And  at this "True blue", we listeners must notice the delicate interplay between the solo vocal of Madonna and the  back  chorus. Such musical skills were called counterpoints in the era of J.S Bach. Anyway, such a distinctly steady song would be apt to become a big hit.

comment: I was the costume designer and stylist on set for this video. Super-fun gig. Love to see it coming around again. This was shot on a sound stage in Queens, and directed by James Foley. Yup, THAT James Foley. Madonna's dress has 80 separate pieces sewn together so it would move beautifully, and she could dance without it shifting. No stretch material involved. Yes, that's Debi Mazar and the black girl is Erica, a frequent backup dancer for Madonna. The Latina's name I don't recall, she was someone's cute friend. At the time (1986), Madonna and Sean were very much in love, and an adorable couple.

comment:
Pat Leonard was the Virgin Tour musical director,  but as the True Blue album co-producer helped Madonna create the definitive commercial sound.
The debut album Madonna (1983), was a collection of disparate songs, while the subtle Like A Virgin album (1984) was a sound development.
With certain True Blue songs, Madonna captured her trademark style - rhythmic, dramatic, distinctively melodic & danceable.
Madonna also felt euphoric cause it was the 1st album she co-produced.

comment: Madonna is Madonna. She is certainly not a scam. She has written, co-written, co-produced and recorded some of the greatest pop music of the last 30+ years. Her videos are the stuff of legend. Her live performances are awesome from the very first Virgin Tour through Blond Ambition, Girlie Show, Confessions up to the last MDNA tour. She is an underrated pop melodist and lyricist. People like Nile Rodgers, Rick Nowels, David Forster, Mirwais etc are all on record saying just this. But people hate to think some little white lady has that much creativity in her. I'm an ex-dancer and dance teacher and I bow down to Madonna as a technically brilliant dancer with that extra special something. Her vocals in the studio, particularly on her ballads, are gorgeous. Her voice is utterly unique and distinctive. The True Blue and Like a Prayer albums are classics in the pop pantheon and Ray of Light and Confessions on a Dance Floor rank among the greatest and most cohesive pop albums of the last 15 years. Obviously one can dislike Madonna and her music but she is the real deal and she achieved all this long before Youtube and the internet. I saw her in December 1982 and January 1983 at Danceteria and she was the best thing there those nights. The only good thing there, actually!

comment: TRUE BLUE pieseň MADONNY vl.m. Veronica  Louise Ciccone nar. 16. augusta 1958 v Rochestri, ktorá bola v UK rebríčku 14 týždňov od 4. oktobra 1986 a ako 577. hit skončila dňa 11. oktobra na týždeň vrchole rebríčka.Madonna sa stala prvou americkou speváčkou s tromi hitmi č.1. po Into The Groove a Papa Don´t Preach .Autormi piesne boli Madonna a Stephen Bray.Od BPI dostala za predaj striebornú platňu. V USA bola v rebríčku 16 týždňov od 4. oktobra 1986 a na tri týždne skončila na 3.m.od 15. novembra kým na vrchole sa striedali Amanda od Boston, Human od Human Leaugue a You Give Love A Bad Name skupiny Bon Jovi.Od RIAA dostala zlatú platňu. Bola to titulná pieseň albumu TRUE BLUE, ktorý v UK bol v rebríčku 85 týždňov od 12. júla 1986 kedy skončil priamo na vrchole spoločne s piesňou Papa Son´t Preach a zotrval tam 6 týždňov a za predaj dostal od BPI 7 platinových platní. S počtom 1 970 000 kusov sa stal najpredávanejším albumom roka 1986 a skončil na 53.m. v TOP 100 BEST SELLING ALBUMS v UK. Madonna v historickom rebríčku s počtom 63 piesni v TOP 10 skončila na 3.m. za Presleym a Cliffom Richardom. V UK počas svojej kariery predala 17,1 miliona kusov singlov. Najpredávanejším albumom sa stal THE IMMACULATE COLLECTION s počtom 3 550 000 kusov a 12 platinovými platňami, ktorý skončil na 4.m. TOP 40 ARTIST COMPILATION ALBUMS OF ALL TIME.

comment:
Linda, simples, bem produzido, básico, elegante, honesto, limpo, romântico, polido, fresco e tudo de bom em som, letras e imagens. 

Esta canção e do resto do álbum True Blue são obras absolutamente incríveis de arte de A a Z. Anos passados, mas este álbum em conjunto com outras Madonna libera a partir dos anos 80 têm realmente aumentado em valor artístico. Eles são totalmente gemas de arte. Poucos álbuns tiveram este tipo de qualidade e poder de permanência. Ninguém está na liga de Madonna. Ela tem e ela permanece em uma liga própria.
